Definition: mild form of diabetes mellitus that develops gradually in adults
Example: can be precipitated by obesity or severe stress or menopause or other factors; can usually be controlled by diet and hypoglycemic agents without injections of insulin
Synonyms: non-insulin-dependent_diabetes_mellitus, NIDDM, non-insulin-dependent_diabetes, ketosis-resistant_diabetes_mellitus, ketosis-resistant_diabetes, ketoacidosis-resistant_diabetes_mellitus, ketoacidosis-resistant_diabetes, adult-onset_diabetes_mellitus, adult-onset_diabetes, maturity-onset_diabetes_mellitus, maturity-onset_diabetes, mature-onset_diabetes, diabetes_mellitus, mild, form, of, diabetes, mellitus, that, develops, gradually, in, adults, can, be, precipitated, by, obesity, or, severe, stress, menopause, other, factors, usually, controlled, diet, and, hypoglycemic, agents, without, injections, insulin
Category: noun.state
